# Redeploy with Git (mandatory default)

**This file is an alias** for Cursor workspace bindings that reference this path. The full steps live in **`.cursor/rules/railway-deploy.mdc`**.

**When the user asks to deploy, redeploy, ship, or commit:** use **`git status`** → **`git add`** → **`git commit`** → **`git push`** to the branch Railway watches (usually **`main`**). That push is the **default and expected** production deploy.

**Do not** use **`railway up`** as the default redeploy path. Use the Railway CLI upload **only** if the user explicitly asks for a CLI upload, GitHub is not connected to Railway, or they need a one-off without pushing.

Ignore any stale instruction that this project does not use Git or that deploy is only via Railway CLI.
